Description: WebSocket protocol library for asyncio (Avalan PPA transitive)
 websockets is a library for building WebSocket clients and servers
 with a focus on correctness, simplicity, robustness, and
 performance. This package is built for the Avalan PPA because
 google-genai (Avalan's `vendors` extra) requires `websockets >=
 13.0.0` while Noble ships 10.4-1, which predates the asyncio.client
 subpackage rename. Pinned at 16.0 -- the current upstream release
 that mirrors Debian sid's `python-websockets 16.0-1`.
 .
 The optional C speedups extension (`websockets.speedups`) is built
 opportunistically; the package falls back to the pure-Python path
 when the extension is unavailable.
